class Solution {
    public int minSwaps(String s) {
        int imbalance = 0, swaps = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '[') {
                imbalance--;
            } else {
                imbalance++;
            }
            swaps = Math.max(swaps, (imbalance + 1) / 2);
        }
        return swaps;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string, tracking the imbalance between opening and closing brackets. It calculates the maximum imbalance encountered, and the minimum swaps required is half of this maximum imbalance rounded up. This approach efficiently solves the problem by making a single pass through the input string.
